rest_of_day_open: It's going to be very busy.  I have a ton of work to get through, and not near enough time to do it.  My husband is working late, so I'm going to have to feed the kids as well.  I'll struggle for downtime, but I am looking forward to Thanksgiving!
critical_positive: We had a lot of common interests.  We both like animals and sports.  We both like to laugh and have fun.  We shared a bit about our families and our personal lives.  There were few uncomfortable silences.  We both went and made the best of it and had a really good time.
critical_negative: The video lagged for a second or two, but I could still hear him.  It's awkward when you meet someone for the first time, so there was a bit of getting to know you.  My dog was acting up in the background and it was a bit distracting.  Not many issues.

rest_of_day_open: I’m not happy this week as convid lockdowns are now more restrictive and I worry about what my kids are going to do for socialization and entertainment. I also have a lot of stressful things coming up at work that I would prefer to go away. Im hoping by the end of the week things will be getting better.
critical_positive: My chat partner was very talkative so their was no awkward silences. She liked to talk a lot about herself so it was very easy on my end to just listen. She also seemed to have questions pre thought out to help keep it going. Overall she was friendly and laughed a lot so it was a pleasant exchange.
critical_negative: My partner tended to try and dominate the conversation. At times when I tried to steer the conversation to another topic she would switch it back to talking about her dog. This wasn’t a huge problem but it did give the impression she wasn’t listening to me at times. This was not offensive by any means.
